textAnnotations.description:
DEDICATED
FOR IAN HAMILTON
THE TWO OLD MEN"
THEY WALKED THESE PATas ON MANY DAYS
WITR TREIR STICKS TO KEEP THEM STEADY,
EACH OF THEM HELPING TRE OTHER OVER
THE ROUGH GROUND.
TREY WOULD CHAT TO STRANGERS Wao WERE
TOURING, SEYTING OUT TAz BEST VIEWS,
TELLING THE ODD STORY FOR OME HAD 3EEN
A PLOUGH MAN THE OTRER A TOWNY FROM GLASGOW.
THEN ON THEIR OWN AGAIN THEY WOULD TURN
To EACE OTHER AND SAY " WE ARE A PAIR OF
DAFT OLD BUGGERS ". FOR WE WERE TROSE
TW) OLD MEN.
FRED.
